<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Burmah Castrol expands in India
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Burmah Castrol, through its Foseco chemicals subsidiary, is buying a
controlling interest in its metallurgical chemicals joint venture in India
for Pounds 155,000.
It increased its stake from 50 per cent to 51 per cent by purchasing new
shares in the venture. Greaves, Burmah's partner, has sold most of its
shares to the public, the balance being reserved for preferential allocation
to the venture's employees.
</TEXT>
