FT  25 JAN 94 / Observer: Brain dead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Bad news for the seedy CD-Rom industry. A Japanese court has ruled that a
ban on a strip-tease computer game is constitutional. Gainax, manufacturers
of Electronic Brain Academy Scenario 1  - the game in question  - failed to
persuade the Miyazaki district court that the ban violated its freedom of
expression.
The judge ruled that the game, which involved a schoolgirl removing an item
of clothing each time a question was answered correctly, 'could give rise to
considerable stimulation of sexual feelings in youth', and would 'develop in
young men the wrong view that girls are tools that exist to satisfy their
sexual demands'. Back to the drawing board presumably.
