Securities and Futures Authority, the self-regulatory organisation for the
professional securities business. At APCIMS he succeeds Michael Baker, who
has been in the post three years.
Turner, above, has been at the SFA and its forerunner - The Securities
Association - since 1988. Prior to that he had spent 15 years at the Stock
Exchange and was latterly involved there in a variety of issues leading up
to Big Bang. As head of membership there, he devised new rules to encompass
the market's new international firms.
APCIMS is the trade association promoting the interests of private client
stockbrokers and investment managers.
