FT  25 JAN 94 / Minister raps council over Tupe
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Tony Baldry, environment minister, yesterday ruled that
Langbaurgh-on-Tees Borough Council, Cleveland, acted anti-competitively when
it refused to disclose details of its workforce's pay and conditions to a
private company bidding for a contract.
The council believed the Transfer of Undertakings (Public Employees)
regulations (Tupe) covered the contract, which meant the bidder would be
obliged to accept the workforce on existing terms and conditions. But it
refused to say what these were because its own workforce was bidding for the
contract. It will now have to offer the contract again.
