FT  25 JAN 94 / Ex-chief of Efim arrested
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LANE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The former chairman of the Efim state holding corporation, Mr Gaetano
Mancini, has been arrested on charges of false accounting and fraud. Italian
police are also seeking the former chairman of Efim's Alumix aluminium
subsidiary, Mr Corrado Innocenti.
The charges relate to consultancy fees paid when Efim's aluminium sector was
restructured at the end of the 1980s. Investigators are examining
allegations that fees in a L5.3bn (Pounds 2m) contract awarded to the
Moberis consultancy firm were swollen to provide L1.5bn in kickbacks.
Mr Mancini, 70, was the last chairman at Efim, whose large losses and heavy
indebtedness underlay the government's decision in July 1992 that it should
be placed in liquidation.
