<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JAN 94 / C&amp;W to invest Pounds 27m in undersea cabling
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW ADONIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cable &amp; Wireless, the UK telecommunications group, is to invest about
Dollars 40m (Pounds 27m) in a new undersea cable system for the eastern
Caribbean, in a significant upgrading of its long-distance capacity in the
region.
The system, 1,730km long, will link 14 islands in the eastern Caribbean from
the British Virgin islands in the north to Trinidad in the south.
It will provide a platform for the region's telecoms needs for the
foreseeable future, underlining C&amp;W's long-term commitment to the region.
The cost of the system is expected to be Dollars 60m. France Telecom and
AT&amp;T, the US long-distance operator, will take initial investment shares of
18 per cent and 6 per cent respectively. C&amp;W's initial share is 66 per cent
of the Dollars 60m project.
C&amp;W has 29 businesses across the Bermuda, Caribbean and Atlantic region. Its
main holding is a 70 per cent stake in Telecommunications of Jamaica, which
made pre-tax profits of USDollars 44.8m last year on revenue of USDollars
175m. It has a 75 per cent stake in Barbados Telephone Company and an
exclusive franchise in Cayman.
</TEXT>
