<HEADLINE>
FT  24 JAN 94 / Independent plan to be announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A consortium led by Mr Andreas Whittam Smith, main founder of The
Independent newspaper, is expected to announce today that it has reached
agreement on a package to restructure the loss-making company.
Under the deal, Mirror Group Newspapers has agreed to take a 40 per cent
stake and the two main existing continental shareholders, El Pais of Spain
and La Repubblica of Italy, will increase their stakes from a present total
of about 38 per cent to 51 per cent. The remainder will be held by the
founding directors and staff.
It is believed a price has not yet been agreed for the shares.
Under the proposed new arrangement, Mr Whittam Smith will become chairman of
a seven-strong board and remain editor-in-chief.
O'Reilly's standpoint, Page 9
