</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MPs to debate policy openness MPs will this week consider a Tory
backbencher's bill which seeks to inject more openness into the process of
making monetary policy.
Mr Nicholas Budgen, MP for Wolverhampton South West, is proposing that the
Treasury's periodic instructions to the Bank of England should be published.
His bill would also force a government that wished to change its chief
objective of monetary policy from price stability to draft a parliamentary
order.
